### Test Event-Driven Vehicle Part Update via Docker ApiGateway
### ApiGateway URL: http://localhost:8387
### RabbitMQ Management: http://localhost:15672 (guest/guest)

### Step 1: Check ApiGateway health
GET http://localhost:8387/healthz

### Step 2: Check ApiGateway environment info
GET http://localhost:8387/_gw/env

### Step 3: Create a SupplyPart for testing (via Docker ApiGateway)
POST http://localhost:8387/api/SupplyParts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "claimItemId": "{{$guid}}",
  "partId": "{{$guid}}",
  "description": "Test Part for Event Testing via Docker ApiGateway",
  "newSerialNumber": "TEST-SERIAL-DOCKER-001",
  "shipmentCode": "SHIP-DOCKER-001",
  "shipmentRef": "REF-DOCKER-001",
  "status": "Installed"
}

### Step 4: Update the SupplyPart to trigger event (via Docker ApiGateway)
PUT http://localhost:8387/api/SupplyParts/{{supplyPartId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "{{supplyPartId}}",
  "claimItemId": "{{$guid}}",
  "partId": "{{$guid}}",
  "description": "Updated Test Part - Event Triggered via Docker ApiGateway",
  "newSerialNumber": "UPDATED-SERIAL-DOCKER-002",
  "shipmentCode": "SHIP-DOCKER-002",
  "shipmentRef": "REF-DOCKER-002",
  "status": "Installed"
}

### Step 5: Check VehiclePart via Docker ApiGateway
GET http://localhost:8387/api/VehicleParts/{{partId}}

### Step 6: Direct access to services (bypass ApiGateway)
### WarrantyClaimService: http://localhost:8004/swagger
### PartCatalogService: http://localhost:7071/swagger

### Step 7: Monitor RabbitMQ Management UI
### Go to: http://localhost:15672
### Login: guest/guest
